documentation.text:
This contract stores the details of all the businesses, that are defined by the
Definitions smart contract, generates ids for new businesses and maintains which 
collection/nft is owned by which business. It supports the admin to add/remove 
collections/nfts and manipulating the same.
@author : Hritik Raheja

addBusiness(string,string,uint256,addres.notice: This method creates a business, increments the businessCount, generates a new and unique business Id, adds the business to the businesses array and maintains the mapping of  business Id to its corresponding index in the businesses array.

addCollectionToBusiness(uint256,uint256).notice: This method adds an already listed collection to a business.

addEmployee(uint256,address).notice: This method adds an employee to a business.

addMultipleCollectionsToBusiness(uint256.notice: This methods adds a number of already listed collections to a business.

addMultipleNftsToBusiness(uint256,uint25.notice: This methods adds a number of already listed nfts to a business.

addNftToBusiness(uint256,uint256).notice: This method adds an already listed NFT to a business.

collectionOrNftOwnedByOwnerOrEmployee(ui.notice: This method checks whether a collection or an nft is owned by the admin or any of the employees or not.

constructor.notice: The deployed NFT and Collections smart contract's addresses are provided as parameters in the constructor in order to create the instances of the contracts.

createCollectionInBusiness(uint256,strin.notice: This methods creates a new collection and adds it to a business.

createNftInBusiness(uint256,string,uint2.notice: This methods creates a new nft and adds it to a business.

getBusinessAdminByBusinessId(uint256).notice: This method returns the admin address of the respective business ID.

getBusinessFeePercentByBusinessId(uint25.notice: This method returns the fee percentage charged by the respective business ID.

getCollectionsInBusiness(uint256).notice: This method fetches the collections owned by a business.

getEmployeesinBusiness(uint256).notice: This method fetches all the employee addresses that are working in a business.

getNftsInBusiness(uint256).notice: This method fetches the nfts owned by a business.

removeBusiness(uint256).notice: This method removes a business from the marketplace, i.e., it removes the business from the businesses array, decrements the businessCount and removes the businessIdToindex  mapping for the particular business Id.

removeCollectionFromBusiness(uint256,uin.notice: This method removes a collection from the business.

removeEmployee(uint256,address).notice: This methods removes an employeee from a business.

removeNftFromBusiness(uint256,uint256).notice: This method removes a nft from the business.

setMarketplaceAddress(address).notice: This method sets the marketplace contract address for super admin validations. This method is called for the first time when the marketplace contract is created, and  can be called again but only by the super admin itself.

updateFeePercent(uint256,uint256).notice: This methods updates the feePercent of the business by the provided fee percent.

userdoc.notice: This contract stores the details of all the businesses, that are defined by the Definitions smart contract, generates ids for new businesses and maintains which  collection/nft is owned by which business. It supports the admin to add/remove  collections/nfts and manipulating the same.
